Parametric Bootstrapping Estimates of Indirect Effect in a Simple Mediation Model for Data Generated from a Multivariate Normal Distribution

Source: R/pbmvn_mar.R
mvn_pbmvn_mar.Rd

Parametric Bootstrapping Estimates of Indirect Effect in a Simple Mediation Model for Data Generated from a Multivariate Normal Distribution

mvn_pbmvn_mar(data, taskid, B = 5000)

Arguments

data

n by 3 matrix or data frame. data[, 1] correspond to values for x. data[, 2] correspond to values for m. data[, 3] correspond to values for y.
taskid

Numeric. Task ID.
B

Integer. Number of bootstrap samples.

See also

Other parametric functions: .pbmvn(), mvn_pbmvn_mar_pcci_simulation(), mvn_pbmvn_mar_pcci_task(), mvn_pbmvn_mar_simulation(), mvn_pbmvn_mar_task(), mvn_pbmvn_mcar_pcci_simulation(), mvn_pbmvn_mcar_pcci_task(), mvn_pbmvn_mcar_simulation(), mvn_pbmvn_mcar_task(), mvn_pbmvn_mcar(), mvn_pbmvn_pcci_simulation(), mvn_pbmvn_pcci_task(), mvn_pbmvn_simulation(), mvn_pbmvn_task(), mvn_pbmvn(), mvn_std_pbmvn_pcci_simulation(), mvn_std_pbmvn_pcci_task(), mvn_std_pbmvn_simulation(), mvn_std_pbmvn_task(), mvn_std_pbmvn(), pbmvn()

Examples

taskid <- 1
data <- mvn_dat(taskid = taskid)
mvn_pbmvn_mar(data = data, taskid = taskid, B = 200)
